<TITLE> Yusuf Islam concert headed to DVD </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW YORK, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A DVD of Yusuf Islam's first complete concert in 28 years will be released October 23 as 'Yusuf's Cafe.' The March 1 performance at London's Porchester Hall was a promotion for the former Cat Stevens' 2006 album, 'An Other Cup' Several cuts from that project are featured on the Universal Music DVD, as are such favorites as 'Don't Be Shy,' 'Peace Train,' 'Father & Son' and a re-arranged version of 'Wild World.' The DVD also includes the hour-long documentary 'A Few Good Songs,' originally shot for the BBC last year, as well as music videos for 'Heaven/Where True Love Goes,' 'Midday (Avoid City After Dark)' and 'Peace Train. 
